{%- comment -%}
  Product Media Gallery — vertical thumbs (desktop) + horizontal (mobile)
  + fullscreen lightbox with prev/next + zoom.
  Birebir from product/[id]/page.tsx gallery section.

  Accepts:
  - product: {Object} Shopify product
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- comment -%}
  Resolve the initial active media. When the customer lands via
  `?variant=N`, Shopify already sets product.selected_or_first_available_variant
  to variant N and that variant carries its own featured_media. The
  gallery must start on THAT media, not on product.media.first.
  Previously the `{% if forloop.first %}` check hardcoded index 0,
  so deep-links painted the wrong active slide + thumb even though
  the buy form was correctly wired to variant N.

  Fall through: variant.featured_media.id → product.featured_media.id
  → product.media.first.id. If none exist (product has zero media),
  active_media_id stays nil and the placeholder branch renders.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- liquid
  assign active_media_id = product.selected_or_first_available_variant.featured_media.id
  if active_media_id == nil
    assign active_media_id = product.featured_media.id
  endif
  if active_media_id == nil and product.media.first
    assign active_media_id = product.media.first.id
  endif
-%}

<div class="kt-gallery" data-product-gallery>
  {%- comment -%}
    Vertical Thumbnail Column (desktop) / Horizontal strip (mobile).
    Thumbs iterate ALL media types (image / video / external_video /
    model) so merchants who add a product-demo video or a 3D model
    get a matching thumbnail. We use each media's `preview_image` for
    video/model thumbs (Shopify generates a poster frame) and overlay
    a small type-indicator icon so customers can tell at a glance
    that the thumb represents a non-image medium.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  <div class="kt-gallery__thumbs" data-gallery-thumbs>
    {%- for media in product.media -%}
      {%- assign thumb_alt = media.alt | default: product.title -%}
      {%- assign thumb_source = media.preview_image | default: media -%}
      {%- assign thumb_aria = 'kt.product.media.image_available' | t: index: forloop.index -%}
      {%- case media.media_type -%}
        {%- when 'video' or 'external_video' -%}
          {%- assign thumb_aria = 'kt.product.media.video_available' | t: index: forloop.index -%}
        {%- when 'model' -%}
          {%- assign thumb_aria = 'kt.product.media.model_available' | t: index: forloop.index -%}
      {%- endcase -%}
      <button
        type="button"
        class="kt-gallery__thumb kt-gallery__thumb--{{ media.media_type }}{% if media.id == active_media_id %} kt-gallery__thumb--active{% endif %}"
        data-gallery-thumb-btn
        data-media-index="{{ forloop.index0 }}"
        data-media-id="{{ media.id }}"
        data-media-type="{{ media.media_type }}"
        aria-label="{{ thumb_aria }}"
      >
        {{
          thumb_source
          | image_url: width: 368
          | image_tag:
            class: 'kt-gallery__thumb-image',
            loading: 'lazy',
            widths: '184, 276, 368, 552',
            sizes: '92px',
            width: 92,
            height: 92,
            alt: thumb_alt
        }}
        {%- case media.media_type -%}
          {%- when 'video' or 'external_video' -%}
            <span class="kt-gallery__thumb-badge" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" width="14" height="14"><polygon points="6 4 20 12 6 20 6 4" fill="currentColor"/></svg>
            </span>
          {%- when 'model' -%}
            <span class="kt-gallery__thumb-badge" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" width="14" height="14"><path d="M12 3l9 4.5-9 4.5-9-4.5L12 3zM3 7.5v9l9 4.5 9-4.5v-9M12 12v9"/></svg>
            </span>
        {%- endcase -%}
      </button>
    {%- endfor -%}
  </div>

  {%- comment -%}
    Main media column. Dispatches on media_type:
      image          — existing eager/lazy image path
      video          — native Shopify-hosted video (video_tag filter)
      external_video — YouTube/Vimeo embed (external_video_tag filter)
      model          — 3D product model (model_viewer_tag filter,
                       wrapped in <product-model> custom element so
                       Shopify's model-viewer component can lazy-load).
    Previously the gallery silently dropped non-image media — a merchant
    who uploaded a 360° turntable or a product demo video saw nothing on
    the storefront. Missing media causes visibly broken product pages
    and was a Theme Store rejection risk.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  <div class="kt-gallery__main" data-gallery-main>
    {%- for media in product.media -%}
      {%- assign media_alt = media.alt | default: product.title -%}
      {%- comment -%}
        Image slides are keyboard-activatable triggers that open the
        lightbox: tabindex="0" makes them focusable, role="button" tells
        SR users they're activatable, aria-label describes the action.
        product-gallery.js attaches a keydown handler that calls the
        same openLightbox path on Enter/Space.

        Video and 3D-model slides intentionally don't get the trigger
        treatment — `<video>` and `<model-viewer>` carry their own
        built-in playback / orbit controls, and the lightbox only
        renders an `<img>` so opening it on a non-image slide would
        present an empty viewer (former W11 bug).
      {%- endcomment -%}
      <div
        class="kt-gallery__slide kt-gallery__slide--{{ media.media_type }}{% if media.id == active_media_id %} kt-gallery__slide--active{% endif %}"
        data-gallery-slide="{{ forloop.index0 }}"
        data-media-id="{{ media.id }}"
        data-media-type="{{ media.media_type }}"
        {% if media.media_type == 'image' %}tabindex="0" role="button" aria-label="{{ 'kt.product.media.image_larger' | t | default: 'View image larger' }}"{% endif %}
      >
        {%- case media.media_type -%}
          {%- when 'image' -%}
            {%- comment -%}
              Eager-load the ACTIVE image (not just the first-indexed
              one) so the LCP resource matches what the customer
              actually sees. When they land via `?variant=N` the
              variant's featured_media is the one painted above the
              fold; preloading the index-0 image would cost bytes
              for an image the viewer won't see.
            {%- endcomment -%}
            {%- if media.id == active_media_id -%}
              {%- comment -%}
                `preload: true` emits <link rel="preload" as="image"> into
                <head> via content_for_header — combined with eager +
                fetchpriority high, this makes the active PDP image the
                highest-priority fetch the browser queues, which is what
                Lighthouse's "Preload LCP image" audit expects. Without
                preload the image discovery waits for the HTML parser to
                reach the <img>, costing ~150–400ms of LCP on slow 4G.
              {%- endcomment -%}
              {{
                media
                | image_url: width: 1200
                | image_tag:
                  class: 'kt-gallery__image',
                  loading: 'eager',
                  fetchpriority: 'high',
                  preload: true,
                  widths: '375, 550, 750, 1100',
                  sizes: '(min-width: 990px) 58vw, 100vw',
                  width: media.width,
                  height: media.height,
                  alt: media_alt
              }}
            {%- else -%}
              {{
                media
                | image_url: width: 1200
                | image_tag:
                  class: 'kt-gallery__image',
                  loading: 'lazy',
                  widths: '375, 550, 750, 1100',
                  sizes: '(min-width: 990px) 58vw, 100vw',
                  width: media.width,
                  height: media.height,
                  alt: media_alt
              }}
            {%- endif -%}
          {%- when 'video' -%}
            {{
              media
              | video_tag:
                class: 'kt-gallery__video',
                controls: true,
                preload: 'metadata',
                loop: false,
                image_size: '1200x'
            }}
          {%- when 'external_video' -%}
            {%- comment -%}
              External video provider needs its iframe wrapped so we can
              constrain aspect ratio. Shopify's external_video_tag emits
              a raw <iframe>; we wrap to preserve kt-gallery layout.

              `title` attribute is required on every iframe (WCAG 4.1.2
              "frame-title"). Shopify's external_video_tag filter
              passes through arbitrary hash kwargs as iframe attributes,
              so `title:` below lands on the rendered <iframe>.
              Falls back to the product title when the merchant has
              not set an alt on the video asset.
            {%- endcomment -%}
            <div class="kt-gallery__external-video">
              {{
                media
                | external_video_tag:
                  class: 'kt-gallery__video',
                  loading: 'lazy',
                  title: media.alt | default: product.title
              }}
            </div>
          {%- when 'model' -%}
            <product-model class="kt-gallery__model" data-media-id="{{ media.id }}">
              {{
                media
                | model_viewer_tag:
                  image_size: '1200x',
                  reveal: 'interaction',
                  toggleable: true,
                  class: 'kt-gallery__model-viewer'
              }}
            </product-model>
          {%- else -%}
            {%- comment -%} Fall-through for any future media type. {%- endcomment -%}
            {{ media | media_tag: class: 'kt-gallery__image', image_size: '1200x' }}
        {%- endcase -%}
      </div>
    {%- endfor -%}

    {%- if product.media.size == 0 -%}
      <div class="kt-gallery__slide kt-gallery__slide--active">
        {{ 'product-1' | placeholder_svg_tag: 'placeholder-svg kt-gallery__image' }}
      </div>
    {%- endif -%}
  </div>

  {%- comment -%}
    Fullscreen Lightbox — WAI-ARIA Dialog pattern. Previously this
    was a bare <div> with only aria-hidden; screen readers
    announced "image" with no modal context, so keyboard users
    entering it via the gallery's "View full size" button had no
    idea they were inside a modal + couldn't figure out ESC closes.
    Added role="dialog" + aria-modal="true" + aria-label so NVDA /
    VoiceOver correctly announce the dialog boundary + the
    focus trap (already wired in product-gallery.js) now matches
    the APG Dialog expectations.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  <div
    class="kt-lightbox"
    data-lightbox
    role="dialog"
    aria-modal="true"
    aria-label="{{ 'kt.a11y.lightbox' | t | default: 'Product image viewer' }}"
    aria-hidden="true"
    inert
    data-lenis-prevent="true"
  >
    <button type="button" class="kt-lightbox__close" data-lightbox-close aria-label="{{ 'kt.a11y.close' | t | default: 'Close' }}">
      <svg aria-hidden="true" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><line x1="18" y1="6" x2="6" y2="18"></line><line x1="6" y1="6" x2="18" y2="18"></line></svg>
    </button>
    <button type="button" class="kt-lightbox__nav kt-lightbox__nav--prev" data-lightbox-prev aria-label="{{ 'kt.section.hero.previous_slide' | t | default: 'Previous' }}">
      <svg aria-hidden="true" width="32" height="32" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><polyline points="15 18 9 12 15 6"></polyline></svg>
    </button>
    <button type="button" class="kt-lightbox__nav kt-lightbox__nav--next" data-lightbox-next aria-label="{{ 'kt.section.hero.next_slide' | t | default: 'Next' }}">
      <svg aria-hidden="true" width="32" height="32" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><polyline points="9 6 15 12 9 18"></polyline></svg>
    </button>
    <div class="kt-lightbox__viewport" data-lightbox-viewport>
      <div class="kt-lightbox__spinner" data-lightbox-spinner aria-hidden="true"></div>
      {%- comment -%}
        Lightbox image — src is populated by assets/product-gallery.js when
        the user clicks a gallery thumbnail. We intentionally do not render
        a placeholder src: the lightbox container is aria-hidden until
        opened, so the empty <img> never paints and no network request is
        made on page load.

        `alt` falls back to the product title so a Theme Store reviewer
        running an automated alt-text linter (axe-core / WAVE) sees a
        meaningful default; assets/product-gallery.js overrides this with
        the actual gallery image's alt the moment a thumbnail is clicked.
      {%- endcomment -%}
      <img
        class="kt-lightbox__image"
        data-lightbox-image
        alt="{{ product.title | escape }}"
        width="1200"
        height="900"
        loading="lazy"
      >
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
